Parliament, Thursday, 29 August 2019 – The Standing Committee on Appropriations invite stakeholders and interested parties to make written submissions on the Special Appropriation Bill [B10-2019]. The Bill was tabled in Parliament by the Minister of Finance on 23 July 2019. The Bill provides for the appropriation of an additional amount of money for the requirements of the Department of Public Enterprises to assist Eskom Holdings SOC Limited with its financial obligations and to provide for matters connected therewith. Public Hearings will be conducted in Parliament on Wednesday, 11 September 2019. Written Submissions must be received by no later than 12:00 on Friday, 6 September 2019. Submissions must be directed to the Committee Secretary, Mr Darrin Arends, 3rd Floor, 90 Plein Street, Cape Town, 8000 or daarends@parliament.gov.za (021) 403-8105 or fax: 0866 374 444. Copies of the 2019 Special Appropriation Bill are available at www.parliament.gov.za and www.treasury.gov.za. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS, MR SFISO BUTHELEZI. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact: Name: Felicia Lombard
